{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"PLAN VERIFIED CLEAN (evidence for the operator-attested import AC). After importing 17 resources into rebar state, `terraform plan` = **1 to add, 10 to change, 0 to destroy, 0 to replace**:\n- add: aws_ssm_parameter.rebar_secrets[\"/rebar/prod/rebar-bot-signing-key\"] — pre-existing intended placeholder (commit 586302cf2), created as CHANGEME.\n- change (all in-place, non-functional): retag project=snap-demo/managed-by/root -> Project=rebar on the 9 taggable adopted resources; aws_iam_role.gha_terraform_plan assume-policy re-render (now references the managed OIDC .arn, resolves to the identical ARN+conditions); aws_route53_record.cert_validation gets allow_overwrite=true (TF-only meta, no DNS change); aws_lambda_function.auth_host code redeploy from rebar's copied source (verified byte-behavior-identical to the deployed zip — the checked-in source was prettier-reformatted after the last deploy; trailing-comma/quote-style only, no logic change — REQUIRED so state source_code_hash matches the committed archive and drift CI stays clean).\n- NO secret rotation: random_password.auth_origin_secret imported with its live value (ignore_changes=[special] suppresses the import-default replacement); cookie-signing SSM value preserved via ignore_changes=[value]. Verified live ORIGIN_SECRET matches state; cookie value untouched."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784047527331320001,"uuid":"0c27a5c0-0ac4-4ec0-9f98-70d65c919e9e"}